'''Plateau Preston Rex "Red" Cox''' (February 16, 1895 <U+2013> October 15, 1984) was an [[United States|American]] professional baseball player who [[pitcher|pitched]] one season in [[Major League Baseball]], appearing in three games for the [[1920 Detroit Tigers season|1920 Detroit Tigers]] of the [[American League]].  In five [[innings pitched]], he allowed three [[earned run]]s, three [[base on balls|bases on balls]], and [[strikeout|struck out]] one batter.<ref name=retrocox>{{cite web|title=Red Cox|url=http://www.retrosheet.org/boxesetc/C/Pcox-r101.htm|work=retrosheet.org|publisher=Retrosheet, Inc|accessdate=March 2, 2011}}</ref>

In addition to his major league experience, he played three seasons of [[minor league baseball]], from 1920 to 1922.<ref name=coxminors>{{cite web|title=Red Cox (minors)|url=http://www.baseball-reference.com/minors/player.cgi?id=cox---001pla|work=baseball-reference.com|publisher=Sports Reference LLC|accessdate=March 2, 2011}}</ref>  He died at the age of 89 in [[Roanoke, Virgina]],  and is interred at Mountain View Cemetery in [[Vinton, Virginia]].<ref name=retrocox/>

